{
  "texts": [
    "For the left-to-right inclusion, suppose x ̸ ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ ■ i X.",
    "If x ̸ ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩, then x ̸ ∈ S ′, so x ̸ ∈ ■ ′ i X ′.",
    "So suppose x ∈ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ but x ̸ ∈ ■ i X, so there is a y such that xR i y and y ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Then by refinability for X, there is a minimal point b ⊑ y such that b ̸ ∈ X and hence b ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "From xR i y and b ⊑ y, we have xR ′ i b, which with b ̸ ∈ X ′ implies x ̸ ∈ ■ ′ i X ′."
  ]
}